cs.OS, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS, cs.PL

This paper discusses OS-level virtualization techniques and their application in virtualizing parallel and distributed applications such as HPC clusters. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper also discusses the duplication of Windows services, which is relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper proposes a methodology for service duplication, which involves data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL).
